IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The Organization provides services and supports to the mentally retarded and developmentally disabled community that will assist in sustaining enhancing or creating lifestyle environments that are rewarding people regardless of their particular situations.
IRS990.MissionDesc: The organization provides program services that were authorized under New York State law and regulations via the Office of People with Developmental Disabilities. The services that were provided to the disabled communities serve to sustain enhance and create lifestyle environments that are rewarding to their particular situations.
IRS990.Desc: The Organization operates a Community Habilitation program for people with developmental disabilities. The program focuses on improving individualized skills including social skills development independent life skills training health and fitness support vocational preparation fine arts and music aspirations and utilization of the community as a learning and living environment.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: The Home and Community Base Services program is designed to allow children and youth to participate in developmentally and culturally appropriate services. The program works with children and youths in their homes and communities to support emotional mental academic and social health and growth while they continue to live and further develop in their communities.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: The Organization operates a Day Habilitation program for people with developmental disabilities. The program takes part in and expose the participants to community activities including introducing them to people outside of their immediate community fostering new friendships and assisting them to become more involved in their community. The program also provides an array of activities including independent life skills training.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Form 990 is prepared by the Organization's CPA firm and is submitted to the treasurer record-keeper for a preliminary review and necessary corrections if any. Once the form is reviewed a copy is given to each member of the governing board of directors as well as the executive director for a final review and acceptance for filing with the Internal Revenue Service.

Each director and officer of the organization is required to sign an annual disclosure form related to any potential conflict of interest that involve the scope of services rendered to the organization. Signed disclosures are reviewed and monitored by the board chairperson frequently. All individuals are expected to communicate any possible conflict of interest on an on-going basis.
The process of determining compensation for the executive director and key employees are in large based on industry comparability data and board approval.

All governing documents form 990 financial statements and related non-profit filings are available to the public upon written request either by fax email or first class mailing or on the organization's website.
